 #!Rall316 Resizing the Image #!N #!EC #!N #!N To resize the 
image, simply resize the image window by dragging its borders to 
shrink or expand the window. The image displayed inside the window 
is resized accordingly. Note that the size of the object in 
the Image window is controlled only by the width of the 
window. #!N #!N You can specify an exact Image window size 
by using  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Camera #!EF mode, as described in  #!Lcamset,dxall310 h Precise Camera Settings  #!EL  . 
#!N #!N For more information on resizing windows, see  #!Lresize,dxall286 h Moving and Resizing Windows  #!EL  . 
#!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next Topic #!EF #!N #!N  #!Lrestimg,dxall318 h Restoring Images  #!EL  #!N 
